integral along a complex time path , starting from some initial
time  and ending at a complex final time , where
the imaginary part is given by the inverse temperature 
. The functional integral is taken over all field
configurations which satisfy the periodic boundary condition
 
One convenient choice of the complex time path consists of three
segments, , where  runs along
the real axis from  to some ,  runs
backwards along the time axis from  to , and finally 
runs parallel to the imaginary axis from  to 
